{"type":"message","id":"2b30d0df","parentId":"95215258","timestamp":"2026-03-27T01:12:41.131Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, neutral trend gave S3? That seems wrong. The mock data might not be generating well for the neutral case. Let me check - the issue might be in the `generate_mock_bars` function. With random data and seed 42, the higher_high_count and higher_low_count might accidentally trigger the bullish structure check. Let me run it a few times to see.\n\nActually wait - the mock bars use `close = base + random.gauss(0, 0.5)` which should be around 100. But then `high = close + abs(random.gauss(0.2, 0.15))` and `low = close - abs(random.gauss(0.2, 0.15))`. \n\nThe randomness could be creating higher highs and higher lows even in neutral mode. Let me run it a few times to see what happens.","thinkingSignature":"dd90789d4905d46091275c64c9b3e75b5765ea38fa6fa6b6aa7cdc13bb16fd41"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_thqbsj9oehni_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && for trend in neutral up down exhaustion; do echo -n \"$trend: \"; python3 scripts/al_brooks_a_share_state_labeler.py --trend $trend 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['state_code'], d['state_name'], '| conf:', d['confidence'])\"; done"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17698,"output":293,"cacheRead":22332,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40323,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774573952201,"responseId":"06150c80c2d8bc7935d3d91a33edccfd"}}
{"type":"message","id":"84fab41e","parentId":"2b30d0df","timestamp":"2026-03-27T01:12:41.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_thqbsj9oehni_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"neutral: S3 上升趋势延续 | conf: 0.71\nup: S3 上升趋势延续 | conf: 0.71\ndown: S5 趋势衰减/失败突破 | conf: 0.68\nexhaustion: S3 上升趋势延续 | conf: 0.71"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":161,"aggregated":"neutral: S3 上升趋势延续 | conf: 0.71\nup: S3 上升趋势延续 | conf: 0.71\ndown: S5 趋势衰减/失败突破 | conf: 0.68\nexhaustion: S3 上升趋势延续 | conf: 0.71","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774573961357}}
{"type":"message","id":"7673e5d6","parentId":"84fab41e","timestamp":"2026-03-27T01:13:04.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The results are suspicious - neutral and exhaustion both give S3, and down gives S5. This is likely because the mock data's higher_high_count_10 and higher_low_count_10 are being calculated incorrectly, or the mock data with seed 42 happens to create bullish structures in most cases. \n\nThe issue might be in how I'm computing higher_high_count_10 and higher_low_count_10. My current formula is:\n\n```python\nhh = sum(1 for i in range(1, n-1) if closes[i] > closes[i-1] and closes[i] > closes[i+1])\n\n\n```\n\nBut that's actually calculating local peaks (where closes[i] is higher than both neighbors), not higher highs (where the current high is higher than the previous high). For higher highs, I need to check if highs[i] > highs[i-1] for all prior points, not just immediate neighbors. Let me reconsider the logic here.\n\nActually, a simpler approach would be to count swing highs using a window-based method instead of the full historical comparison. I'll also need to do the same correction for lower lows - checking if lows are lower than all prior lows.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"d980e710256c46138f9f572648a2447a790f63bfa7a0305bd9c2c9e7152441c4"},{"type":"text","text":"The mock data logic has a bug in swing counting. Let me fix the feature computation:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qa0rl9eoplgh_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/al_brooks_a_share_state_labeler.py","oldText":"    # --- 趋势结构组 ---\n    hh = sum(1 for i in range(1, n-1) if closes[i] > closes[i-1] and closes[i] > closes[i+1])\n    hl = sum(1 for i in range(1, n-1) if closes[i] < closes[i-1] and closes[i] < closes[i+1])\n    lh = sum(1 for i in range(1, n-1) if highs[i] < highs[i-1] and highs[i] < highs[i+1])\n    ll = sum(1 for i in range(1, n-1) if lows[i]  > lows[i-1]  and lows[i]  > lows[i+1])\n    higher_high_count_10  = hh\n    higher_low_count_10   = hl\n    lower_high_count_10   = lh\n    lower_low_count_10    = ll","newText":"    # --- 趋势结构组 ---\n    # 简化版：最近10根中，HH=收盘创前高新高次数，HL=收盘创前低新低次数\n    window = min(10, n - 1)\n    hh = sum(1 for i in range(n-window, n)\n             if highs[i] > max(highs[max(0, i-5):i]))\n    ll = sum(1 for i in range(n-window, n)\n             if lows[i] < min(lows[max(0, i-5):i]))\n    # LH/LL 用作下降趋势确认\n    lh = sum(1 for i in range(n-window, n)\n             if highs[i] < min(highs[max(0, i-5):i]))\n    hl = sum(1 for i in range(n-window, n)\n             if lows[i]  > max(lows[max(0, i-5):i]))\n    higher_high_count_10  = hh\n    higher_low_count_10   = hl\n    lower_high_count_10   = lh\n    lower_low_count_10    = ll"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18074,"output":767,"cacheRead":22332,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41173,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774573961367,"responseId":"06150c890b9c5ace8f55d818d16fd82d"}}
