{"type":"message","id":"ace0c26b","parentId":"ad8801f2","timestamp":"2026-03-27T01:13:39.893Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, my definitions are still not quite right. Let me think more carefully.\n\nFor a bullish trend:\n- Higher High (HH): Each successive high is higher than the previous high\n- Higher Low (HL): Each successive low is higher than the previous low\n\nFor the last N bars, counting how many bars make a HH/HL/LH/LL:\n- HH: high[i] > max(highs[:i]) -- current high is a new high relative to all previous bars\n- HL: low[i] > max(lows[:i]) -- current low is a new high relative to all previous lows (in an uptrend, HL keeps going up)\n\n\n- LH: high[i] < min(highs[:i]) -- current high is a new low relative to all previous highs (in a downtrend, LH keeps going down)\n- LL: low[i] < min(lows[:i]) -- current low is a new low relative to all previous bars\n\nSo I need to adjust the window calculation to look at all prior bars, not just the immediately preceding ones.","thinkingSignature":"bf1da538a3cfddb30378510324b0a83799959731b2bd5f8c265c18285ba1f05b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qf1mqnj555x5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && python3 -c \"\nimport ast; ast.parse(open('scripts/al_brooks_a_share_state_labeler.py').read()); print('语法OK')\n\" && echo \"---RUN---\" && for trend in neutral up down exhaustion; do\n  echo -n \"$trend: \"\n  python3 scripts/al_brooks_a_share_state_labeler.py --trend $trend 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['state_code'], d['state_name'], '| conf:', d['confidence'], '| HH:', d['features']['higher_high_count_10'], 'HL:', d['features']['higher_low_count_10'], 'LH:', d['features']['lower_high_count_10'])\"\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":19857,"output":416,"cacheRead":22332,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42605,"cost":{"input":0,"outp