{"type":"message","id":"a09ea847","parentId":"3fc9926c","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:50:33.203Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand P1-001. The issue is about consistency between runtime status, report status, and event_watch status:\n\n1. `runtime=normal, report=halt` — runtime says normal but report says halt\n2. `runtime_halt=False, report_halt=True` — same issue, different field names\n3. `runtime stale vs report` — runtime data is from 11:00:18, report from 11:35:11 (different timestamps)\n4. `event_watch_source=paper_profiles` — event_watch uses paper_profiles as source\n5. `event_watch_mode=halt, runtime=normal` — event_watch says halt, runtime says normal\n\n\n6. `event_watch_halt=True, runtime_halt=False` — same inconsistency with halt flags\n\nSo the core problem is that three different components are reading from different data sources and reaching contradictory conclusions about market state. I need to trace where each one pulls its data from and establish which should be the authoritative source.","thinkingSignature":"ece7e354cad7bc7c35abde2327cf4b7f53f08ec6ac9b34d72159e5e2884be6d0"},{"type":"text","text":"\nP1-001 问题清晰：`runtime` / `report` / `event_watch` 三个组件数据源不统一，导致 halt/normal 判断互相矛盾。先定位各组件的真实数据入口：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1r0k8nydqpf5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"runtime_halt\\|report_halt\\|event_watch\\|runtime.*=\\|report.*=\\|halt.*=\" scripts/run_quant_p0_audit.py 2>/dev/null | head -40","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":32229,"output":340,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55601,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583422423,"responseId":"0615317eeee4bbfcf25dbbd70003ebd0"}}
