{"type":"message","id":"cd598a67","parentId":"a53eed68","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:51:52.345Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the problem more clearly.\n\nLooking at the script logic:\n- Line 421: `risk_mode = str(runtime_snapshot.get(\"mode\") or resolve_risk_mode(profile_stats) or \"mixed\")`\n- Line 424: `halt_new_buy = to_bool(runtime_snapshot.get(\"halt_new_buy\"))`\n- Line 429: `risk_mode = resolve_risk_mode(profile_stats)`\n- Line 432: `halt_new_buy = all(to_bool(stats.get(\"halt_new_buy\")) for stats in profile_stats) if profile_stats else False`\n\n\n- The runtime_snapshot is pulling from `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` at line 404, but the issue is that this file gets updated by this same script, so when it runs multiple times, it might be reading stale or inconsistent data from earlier in the same execution cycle.\n\nLet me trace through what the precheck script does to see if it's the one actually creating the halt condition that then gets propagated to the strategy report.","thinkingSignature":"4df23a5fc13b92acd2291240630f91ab380c0d9489fccf558d8ccd9785c89f35"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5gj9e4wtspr0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"halt_new_buy\\|risk_mode\\|runtime_risk_state\" scripts/auto_run_premarket_precheck.py 2>/dev/null | head -20; echo \"---\"; ls -lt quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/runtime_risk_state* 2>/dev/null | head -5","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36846,"output":320,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60198,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583502924,"responseId":"061531cfee59a082f90ab50f4dc3ae8e"}}
