{"type":"message","id":"b3683fd2","parentId":"8b57969b","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:53:20.494Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The event_watch script itself comments that `runtime_risk_state` contains intraday realtime gate data that's fresher than the morning strategy report. This confirms the hierarchy.\n\nLet me now read the event_watch script to understand the P1-001 issue better.","thinkingSignature":"be2609e9b10024a8eab5cd42a67e183c4d0e5f342568153371377b43faba5064"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qqtjcvdtiao2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"halt_new_buy\\|mode.*=\\|paper_profiles\\|runtime_risk_state\\b\" scripts/run_investment_research_event_watch.py 2>/dev/null | head -30","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42015,"output":142,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65189,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583596718,"responseId":"0615322cf9ab357201f5b6f458ad615d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"dfce14f1","parentId":"b3683fd2","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:53:20.554Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qqtjcvdtiao2_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"86:                \"halt_new_buy\": latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\"),\n90:                \"allowed_to_open_new_positions\": not bool(latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\")),\n99:    # 注意：第二个 overlay 块不得覆盖第一个 runtime_risk_state 块已设置的字段，\n100:    # 因为 runtime_risk_state 含有盘中实时门控，比 morning strategy report 更新鲜。\n101:    # 只在 runtime_risk_state 无数据时才用 strategy_report 的值做 fallback。\n113:        if report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\") is not None:\n114:            pe.setdefault(\"halt_new_buy\", report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\"))\n115:            pe.setdefault(\"allowed_to_open_new_positions\", not bool(report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\")))"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4,"aggregated":"86:                \"halt_new_buy\": latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\"),\n90:                \"allowed_to_open_new_positions\": not bool(latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\")),\n99:    # 注意：第二个 overlay 块不得覆盖第一个 runtime_risk_state 块已设置的字段，\n100:    # 因为 runtime_risk_state 含有盘中实时门控，比 morning strategy report 更新鲜。\n101:    # 只在 runtime_risk_state 无数据时才用 strategy_report 的值做 fallback。\n113:        if report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\") is not None:\n114:            pe.setdefault(\"halt_new_buy\", report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\"))\n115:            pe.setdefault(\"allowed_to_open_new_positions\", not bool(report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\")))","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774583600543}}
{"type":"message","id":"4c71daab","parentId":"dfce14f1","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:53:35.914Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture of P1-001. Let me understand the consistency problem:\n\n**The P1-001 Issue:**\n\nThere are three data sources for `halt_new_buy` and `mode`:\n\n1. **`runtime_risk_state_latest.json`** (the \"runtime truth source\"):\n   - Written by: primarily `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` OR `run_investment_research_mainline_guard.py` via `generate_control_tower_daily.py`\n   - Current value (11:00): `mode=normal`, `halt_new_buy=False`\n   - This is supposed to be the authoritative source for runtime state\n   \n2. **`today_stock_strategy_report_{date}.json`** (the strategy report):\n   - Also generated by `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py`\n   - Current value (11:35): `risk_mode=halt`, `halt_new_buy=True`\n   - When the report regenerates during intraday with fresher paper_profiles data, it can independently compute `halt=True` even though `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` still shows `halt=False`\n\n3. **`investment_research_event_watch_{date}.json`** (the event watch):\n   - Generated by `run_investment_research_event_watch.py`\n   - Current value (11:45): `mode=halt`\n\nThe core problem is that the strategy report and event watch are both deriving their halt decisions from paper_profiles data, but they're not reading from the same runtime state source. When the strategy report regenerates intraday, it's recomputing halt independently rather than using the authoritative runtime state that the event watch is supposed to reference. The `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` file isn't being updated when the report regenerates, so the runtime source remains stale while the strategy report reflects newer conditions.\n\nThe fix requires ensuring that whenever the strategy report determines a halt state, it immediately updates `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` to stay synchronized, and the event watch should prioritize reading from `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` as the single source of truth rather than falling back to the strategy report.\n\nNow I need to check which script actually writes to `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` — I know `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` reads from it, but I'm not certain if it also writes the updates.","thinkingSignature":"e1de55f09b8e4d3657e03e7f7b7b70afb0b6879c5d192bc55ef119f9bbf4c46c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jjblj43j5u37_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"latest_runtime\\|runtime_risk_state.*json\\|write.*json\\|save_state\\|persist\" quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"^#\" | grep -v \"load\" | head -20","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42341,"output":593,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65966,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583600555,"responseId":"061532301b0f7c5b680bbf23699f5c75"}}
