{"type":"message","id":"171a1119","parentId":"fa370b29","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:54:03.592Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it. `generate_control_tower_daily.py` at line 298 creates the `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`. It loads it (line 686) and writes it via `write_intervention_audit_report` (line 488).\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. `generate_control_tower_daily.py` is the writer of `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`\n2. `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` reads it to build runtime_snapshot\n3. The strategy report generates its own `risk_mode` and `halt_new_buy` from `paper_profiles`, which can differ from what's in `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`\n\n\n4. `run_investment_research_event_watch.py` then reads from `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` and falls back to the strategy report if needed\n\nThe core problem is that `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` independently computes `halt_new_buy` from `paper_profiles` and writes it to the strategy report, but this halt decision never gets propagated back to `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`. So when `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` was written at 11:00 with `mode=normal, halt_new_buy=False`, the strategy report at 11:35 independently calculated `risk_mode=halt, halt_new_buy=True` from the same `paper_profiles` data, creating a mismatch.\n\nThe event watch then reads from both sources and reports `mode=halt` because it's pulling from the strategy report's value, not the runtime state. The real issue is that the strategy report is treating itself as authoritative over the runtime state file, when really the runtime state should be the single source of truth that all other scripts reference. I need to check whether the strategy report is actually writing to the runtime state file or if it's just reading from it.","thinkingSignature":"9516e3118af384095b2b0e8ee3882094dc508b4e2aefb6e295b6f03b87a28536"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_12e43cjgogjb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"wc -l quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py; grep -n \"def.*write\\|def.*save\\|runtime_risk_state_latest.*=\\|write_state\\|write_json\" quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py 2>/dev/null | head -10","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44086,"output":509,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67627,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583631250,"responseId":"0615324f07f4699d85d6029d49964f9c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"311b9ccf","parentId":"171a1119","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:54:03.693Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_12e43cjgogjb_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"797 quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py\n19:def atomic_write_text(path: Path, content: str, *, encoding: str = \"utf-8\") -> None:\n27:def atomic_write_json(path: Path, payload: Any) -> None:\n788:    atomic_write_json(json_path, payload)\n790:    atomic_write_json(latest_json_path, payload)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"797 quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py\n19:def atomic_write_text(path: Path, content: str, *, encoding: str = \"utf-8\") -> None:\n27:def atomic_write_json(path: Path, payload: Any) -> None:\n788:    atomic_write_json(json_path, payload)\n790:    atomic_write_json(latest_json_path, payload)","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774583643682}}
{"type":"message","id":"57669726","parentId":"311b9ccf","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:54:30.824Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` writes to its own report JSON files (lines 788, 790) but does NOT write to `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`. It only reads from `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`.\n\nThe `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` is written by `generate_control_tower_daily.py`.\n\nNow the core issue of P1-001 is clear:\n\n**Root cause:** `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` is the designated authoritative runtime state, but:\n1. It was last written at 11:00 (by `generate_control_tower_daily.py` presumably during morning mainline run)2. `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` at 11:35 independently computed halt from paper_profiles but did NOT update `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`\n\n\n3. The event_watch then pulls halt from the strategy report instead of the authoritative runtime state\n\nThe solution is to ensure that whenever `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` computes a halt decision from paper_profiles, it immediately updates `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` with that decision. I need to verify the file paths first to make sure this write operation targets the correct location.\n\nChecking the path definitions, the `generate_control_tower_daily.py` uses `REPORT_DIR / \"runtime_risk_state_latest.json\"` and the strategy report script does the same, so they're writing to the same location. The fix should add an `atomic_write_json` call to `runtime_risk_state_latest_path` after the halt_new_buy computation completes. However, there's a structural mismatch I need to account for—`runtime_risk_state_latest.json` has a `latest_runtime` sub-object, so I can't just write the halt_new_buy value at the top level.\n\nActually, looking at the existing code, `generate_control_tower_daily.py` already loads `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`, modifies the `latest_runtime` section with values from the strategy report (including halt_new_buy), and writes it back. So the strategy report doesn't need to write directly to that file at all—the control tower handles it during its next run.\n\nThe real issue is the timing gap: `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` gets updated at 11:00, then the strategy report runs at 11:35 and computes a new halt value from paper_profiles, but that value sits in the strategy report without updating the runtime state file until the next control tower execution. Meanwhile, other components like event_watch are reading halt from the strategy report directly instead of waiting for the runtime state to be synced.\n\nThe fix is to make `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` update `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` immediately whenever it computes a halt decision from paper_profiles, ensuring the runtime state stays in sync with the strategy report's computations.\n\nBut there's a timing inconsistency I'm noticing: the runtime state file shows mode=normal while the strategy report shows mode=halt, which suggests they might be computing from different data snapshots or there's a logic gap in how the mode gets resolved when both runtime_snapshot and profile_stats exist.\n\nLooking at the code path, if `runtime_snapshot.get(\"authoritative\")` is True, it reads mode directly from the runtime state file. The problem is that when the strategy report runs later, it re-reads the same stale runtime state file that was written at 11:00, so it gets the old normal mode value even though the profile_stats from the more recent precheck might indicate halt should be true.\n\nThen when halt_new_buy gets computed as True in the strategy report, that newer value doesn't propagate back to update runtime_risk_state_latest.json. The event_watch layer compounds this by checking the strategy report's halt_new_buy value instead of relying solely on the authoritative runtime state, creating a cascade where different components are working with inconsistent halt decisions.\n\nThe solution is to have generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py immediately update runtime_risk_state_latest.json whenever it computes halt_new_buy from the profiles, so the runtime state file stays synchronized with what the strategy report is actually deciding. But the audit findings show event_watch_mode=halt while runtime_mode=normal, which suggests this synchronization isn't happening yet.","thinkingSignature":"30ca0a8779017c003221e3d90b6bed5dd781de23ea4ee3a3fcfb425c80c58011"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3f1qcxs1n60n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd=json.load(open('research/reports/investment_research_event_watch_20260327.json'))\npe = ((d.get('current') or {}).get('paper_execution_status') or {})\nprint('event_watch.source:', pe.get('source'))\nprint('event_watch.mode:', pe.get('mode'))\nprint('event_watch.halt_new_buy:', pe.get('halt_new_buy'))\n# Check what event_watch reads\n\" 2>/dev/null; echo \"---runtime---\"; python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd=json.load(open('quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/runtime_risk_state_latest.json'))\nprint('runtime.mode:', d.get('latest_runtime',{}).get('mode'))\nprint('runtime.halt_new_buy:', d.get('latest_runtime',{}).get('halt_new_buy'))\n\" 2>/dev/null","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44698,"output":1123,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68853,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583643693,"responseId":"0615325b6bb0d40c86374495c8fc5a5e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ea7392a","parentId":"57669726","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:54:30.954Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3f1qcxs1n60n_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"event_watch.source: paper_profiles\nevent_watch.mode: halt\nevent_watch.halt_new_buy: True\n---runtime---\nruntime.mode: normal\nruntime.halt_new_buy: False"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":44,"aggregated":"event_watch.source: paper_profiles\nevent_watch.mode: halt\nevent_watch.halt_new_buy: True\n---runtime---\nruntime.mode: normal\nruntime.halt_new_buy: False","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774583670944}}
{"type":"message","id":"f094547b","parentId":"3ea7392a","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:54:34.107Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me look at how event_watch decides `source=paper_profiles`.","thinkingSignature":"cb96761d6d354c875659042855e99050cab38ccec0021f7a3369e13f08f4ab55"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_byxdog8j1smv_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":60,"limit":80,"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_investment_research_event_watch.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45880,"output":89,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69001,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583670954,"responseId":"06153277ca5decc55a2ebe0450924b9a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b8489caa","parentId":"f094547b","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:54:34.194Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_byxdog8j1smv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"            runtime_obj = {}\n    report_path = QUANT_REPORT_DIR / f\"today_stock_strategy_report_{date_tag}.json\"\n    if not report_path.exists():\n        report_path = QUANT_REPORT_DIR / \"today_stock_strategy_report_latest.json\"\n    if report_path.exists():\n        try:\n            report_obj = load_json(report_path)\n        except Exception:\n            report_obj = {}\n    return runtime_obj, report_obj\n\n\ndef apply_runtime_overlay(summary: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    date_tag = str(summary.get(\"strategy_report_date_tag\") or summary.get(\"paper_date_tag\") or datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\"))\n    runtime_obj, report_obj = load_runtime_overlay(date_tag)\n    latest_runtime = runtime_obj.get(\"latest_runtime\") or {}\n\n    if str(runtime_obj.get(\"date_tag\") or \"\") == date_tag and latest_runtime:\n        summary[\"risk_off\"] = bool(latest_runtime.get(\"risk_off\"))\n        pe = dict(summary.get(\"paper_execution_status\") or {})\n        pe.update(\n            {\n                \"source\": \"runtime_risk_state_latest\",\n                \"mode\": latest_runtime.get(\"mode\"),\n                \"risk_off\": latest_runtime.get(\"risk_off\"),\n                \"hard_stop\": latest_runtime.get(\"hard_stop\"),\n                \"halt_new_buy\": latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\"),\n                \"halt_reason\": latest_runtime.get(\"halt_reason\"),\n                \"market_breadth\": latest_runtime.get(\"market_breadth\"),\n                \"gate_reasons\": latest_runtime.get(\"gate_reasons\") or [],\n                \"allowed_to_open_new_positions\": not bool(latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\")),\n                \"runtime_state_path\": str(RUNTIME_STATE_LATEST),\n            }\n        )\n        summary[\"paper_execution_status\"] = pe\n        source_paths = dict(summary.get(\"source_paths\") or {})\n        source_paths[\"runtime_risk_state_json\"] = str(RUNTIME_STATE_LATEST)\n        summary[\"source_paths\"] = source_paths\n\n    # 注意：第二个 overlay 块不得覆盖第一个 runtime_risk_state 块已设置的字段，\n    # 因为 runtime_risk_state 含有盘中实时门控，比 morning strategy report 更新鲜。\n    # 只在 runtime_risk_state 无数据时才用 strategy_report 的值做 fallback。\n    trade_date_text = str(report_obj.get(\"trade_date\") or \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\")\n    if trade_date_text == date_tag and report_obj and not latest_runtime:\n        pe = dict(summary.get(\"paper_execution_status\") or {})\n        pe.setdefault(\"source\", \"strategy_report\")\n        if report_obj.get(\"risk_mode\") is not None:\n            pe.setdefault(\"mode\", report_obj.get(\"risk_mode\"))\n        if report_obj.get(\"risk_off\") is not None:\n            pe.setdefault(\"risk_off\", report_obj.get(\"risk_off\"))\n            summary.setdefault(\"risk_off\", bool(report_obj.get(\"risk_off\")))\n        if report_obj.get(\"hard_stop\") is not None:\n            pe.setdefault(\"hard_stop\", report_obj.get(\"hard_stop\"))\n        if report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\") is not None:\n            pe.setdefault(\"halt_new_buy\", report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\"))\n            pe.setdefault(\"allowed_to_open_new_positions\", not bool(report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\")))\n        if report_obj.get(\"trigger_reason\"):\n            pe.setdefault(\"halt_reason\", report_obj.get(\"trigger_reason\"))\n        if \"market_breadth\" in report_obj:\n            pe.setdefault(\"market_breadth\", report_obj.get(\"market_breadth\"))\n        summary[\"paper_execution_status\"] = pe\n    return summary\n\n\ndef should_reset_baseline(prev: dict[str, Any] | None, cur: dict[str, Any]) -> tuple[bool, str]:\n    if not prev:\n        return False, \"\"\n\n    prev_dt = parse_dt(prev.get(\"generated_at\"))\n    if prev_dt != datetime.min and (datetime.now() - prev_dt).days >= 2:\n        return True, \"previous_state_stale\"\n\n    prev_source_paths = prev.get(\"source_paths\", {}) or {}\n    old_holdings = str(prev_source_paths.get(\"app_holdings_csv\") or \"\")\n    old_live_report = str(prev_source_paths.get(\"live_system_report\") or \"\")\n    if \"ths_app_holdings_\" in old_holdings or \"live_system_v1\" in old_live_report:\n        return True, \"previous_state_old_execution_regime\"\n\n    if not prev.get(\"paper_date_tag\") and cur.get(\"paper_date_tag\"):\n        return True, \"previous_state_missing_paper_baseline\"\n\n[161 more lines in file. Use offset=140 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774583674182}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc4f15c2","parentId":"b8489caa","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:54:53.269Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I fully understand the P1-001 issue:\n\n**Root Cause Analysis:**\n\n1. `event_watch` has a two-level fallback:\n   - First, it checks if `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` has today's data (`date_tag == date_tag`) AND has `latest_runtime`\n   - If YES → it uses `runtime_risk_state_latest` as source\n   - If NO → it falls back to `today_stock_strategy_report` and sets source=`strategy_report`\n\n2. The problem: `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` has `date_tag=20260327` but its `latest_runtime.mode=normal` (from 11:00). The condition at line 80 (`str(runtime_obj.get(\"date_tag\") or \"\") == date_tag and latest_runtime`) is TRUE because `date_tag` matches and `latest_runtime` exists. So it should be using `runtime_risk_state_latest` as source!\n   \n3. Yet the event_watch shows `source=paper_profiles`, not `runtime_risk_state_latest`. This suggests the condition check is actually failing or being bypassed somehow—either `date_tag` isn't matching what I think it is, or `latest_runtime` is empty despite existing, which would explain why it falls back to the strategy report instead.\n\nLooking at the fallback logic more carefully, I see that `latest_runtime` is being extracted from `runtime_obj` before the condition check even happens. So if `apply_runtime_overlay` is being called with `summary` containing a `paper_execution_status` that already has `source=paper_profiles`, and the condition fails, then the fallback code would use `setdefault()` to preserve that existing source rather than overwriting it. That would explain why the final source ends up as `paper_profiles` instead of `runtime_risk_state_latest`.\n\nThe root issue is that `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` gets populated at 11:00 with `mode=normal`, but `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` doesn't update it when it runs later with fresher `paper_profiles` data that says `mode=halt`. So the runtime state becomes stale while the report has the current state, yet `event_watch` still references the runtime state file.\n\nThe solution is to either have the report update `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` after computing the halt state, or adjust `event_watch` to prefer the report's values when they're more recent. The first approach feels more architecturally sound since it keeps `runtime_risk_state_latest` as the authoritative source.","thinkingSignature":"58602455ca3267c310e0b6f02f29736f03e4cef4371790901d5c00f7d0944d4e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kkpjb630nwdc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"REPORT_DIR\\|QUANT_REPORT\" scripts/run_investment_research_event_watch.py 2>/dev/null | head -10","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46968,"output":615,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70615,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583674194,"responseId":"0615327adb94a09221216ed023cae2f8"}}
