{"type":"message","id":"4324b991","parentId":"51211e1e","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:55:35.565Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` file is likely written by a different mechanism. Let me look at the full flow. Since `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` has a specific structure, it must be written by some script. Let me check what creates this file by looking at its modification time and the scripts that exist.Actually, wait. Let me re-read the key section of `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` around lines 399-435. I see:\n\nLine 399: `if str(runtime_state_latest.get(\"date_tag\") or \"\") == str(date_tag) and latest_runtime:`\n\n\nThis condition determines whether the runtime_snapshot is authoritative — if the date_tag matches and latest_runtime exists, it gets values from runtime_risk_state_latest.json. Otherwise it falls back to profile_stats. The P1-001 issue shows runtime=normal while report=halt, meaning the condition was true and runtime_snapshot came from the runtime state file, but risk_mode resolved to halt from profile_stats instead.\n\nLooking at the code around line 420-432, I see the issue now. When runtime_snapshot is authoritative, it first tries to use runtime_snapshot values, but then immediately overwrites them with resolve_risk_mode(profile_stats) and halt_new_buy computed from all profiles. So even though runtime_snapshot was authoritative and came from runtime_risk_state_latest.json, risk_mode and halt_new_buy are being derived from the profile_stats instead of using the runtime_snapshot values. The runtime_snapshot.authoritative=True flag is misleading because the most critical fields—risk_mode and halt_new_buy—are still being computed from profile_stats rather than taken from the runtime state.\n\nThe cleanest fix is to update runtime_risk_state_latest.json immediately after the strategy report computes halt_new_buy, so that other scripts reading from that file get consistent values. This keeps the runtime state as the single source of truth, which is the architectural intent.","thinkingSignature":"a323c0368d3ce5282c5cd22be62c38a2b18427cce033163467998b8d2c27a738"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jwzp8wq3eupe_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"REPORT_DIR\\|PROJECT_ROOT\" quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py 2>/dev/null | head -5","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50111,"output":480,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73623,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583723043,"responseId":"061532abc293f7f314b087f0039a58bc"}}
