{"type":"message","id":"6f6ed40c","parentId":"c3046f49","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:56:46.135Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, interesting. The `mode` is now `cautious` (not `halt`) and `halt_new_buy` is `False`. Let me check what the strategy report says now.\n\nWait - the mode changed from `normal` to `cautious` and `halt_new_buy` is `False`. But the audit findings said `report=halt` with `halt_new_buy=True`. So either:\n1. The strategy report just computed `cautious` and `halt_new_buy=False` this time (different from before), OR\n2. The `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` was updated by my fix with the new values\n\n\n3. Let me look at the current strategy report to see what it actually says.","thinkingSignature":"7a4d601e67485bf74b492655d7103454989f49a92679f3950af4620985f15600"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_obq599bt4uyq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd=json.load(open('quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/today_stock_strategy_report_2026-03-27.json'))\nprint('report risk_mode:', d.get('risk_mode'))\nprint('report halt_new_buy:', d.get('halt_new_buy'))\nprint('report generated_at:', d.get('generated_at'))\n\"","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":53830,"output":280,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77142,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583799454,"responseId":"061532f7f2c968674ebbb7815804abde"}}
