{"type":"message","id":"4cf710cf","parentId":"05da04e4","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:56:54.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the strategy report now shows `risk_mode=cautious, halt_new_buy=False`, and the runtime_risk_state_latest.json was also updated to `cautious, halt_new_buy=False`. The fix worked - the runtime state is now in sync with the strategy report.\n\nHowever, there's still a question: why did the strategy report compute `cautious/False` this time when the audit showed `halt/True` before? Let me look at the `resolve_risk_mode` function to understand.\n\nActually, looking at the P1-001 findings again - the previous strategy report run (at 11:35) found `halt_new_buy=True` from some paper_profiles, but the current run (at 11:56) found `halt_new_buy=False`. \n\nThe market conditions must have shifted between those two runs, which is fine - the real issue was that the strategy report's halt value wasn't propagating back to the runtime state. Now that my fix is in place, the runtime state stays synchronized with whatever the strategy report computes. Let me run the P0 audit to see if P1-001 shows as resolved.","thinkingSignature":"659b41f6fdc310cf883450e1f807f653f305dc1cf7b8922a51521ba7ba7ef3d0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r4qjg9hs60jr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && python3 scripts/run_quant_p0_audit.py 2>&1 | tail -10","yieldMs":25000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54157,"output":314,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77503,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583806244,"responseId":"061532fefa0a8271feb52c704fb95917"}}
