{"type":"message","id":"b986ff55","parentId":"48dcc6c3","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:57:06.989Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, interesting. The remaining findings are:\n1. `event_watch stale: event_watch=2026-03-27 11:45:06 runtime=2026-03-27 11:56:34` — event_watch is older than runtime\n2. `event_watch_source=paper_profiles` — event_watch is still using paper_profiles as source (not `runtime_risk_state_latest`)\n3. `event_watch_mode=halt, runtime=cautious` — event_watch still has old mode\n4. `event_watch_halt=True, runtime_halt=False` — event_watch still has old halt\n\nThe event_watch is still using old data because it hasn't been regenerated yet. \n\nThe audit is running against a stale event_watch file from 11:45, but my fix should pull fresh runtime values from the updated runtime_risk_state_latest.json that was just written at 11:56. Once event_watch regenerates, it should pick up the correct source and mode. The remaining staleness issue is just a timing gap between when the runtime state was refreshed and when event_watch was last generated.","thinkingSignature":"fa2a43689736a9fb258d861981ddfb1c2ae6993d4e9fc5347c7c26659500224a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kdxcy1yc1ksn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && python3 scripts/run_investment_research_event_watch.py --date 2026-03-27 2>&1 | tail -5","yieldMs":25000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54814,"output":333,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78179,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774583818866,"responseId":"0615330b9528d4b9f744a225dd7527fa"}}
