j.get(\"trigger_reason\")` — I need to see what that value actually is.\n``` The fallback condition checks out — `latest_runtime` is definitely truthy with all those keys populated. So Block 1 should be executing and setting `halt_new_buy=False`, which means something else must be overriding it after that point.\n\nLet me trace through the actual event_watch JSON more carefully. The `paper_execution_status` object has a `mode` field, and I need to see exactly where `\"halt\"` is coming from and whether it's being set after Block 1 runs.","thinkingSignature":"340660c78f57d3e48cd6f01da788548acfaba92f407c4f8e8c6052beb8bd20a8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_650p7pj1jjgj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd=json.load(open('research/reports/investment_research_event_watch_20260327.json'))\npe = ((d.get('current') or {}).get('paper_execution_status') or {})\nprint('ALL pe keys:', list(pe.keys()))\nfor k,v in pe.items():\n    print(f'  {k}: {v}')\n\"","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":63395,"output":665,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87092,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774584030850,"responseId":"061533df4933b0784e833ee36064d5c4"}}
