{"type":"message","id":"eea984a4","parentId":"aa6efbce","timestamp":"2026-03-27T04:00:58.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it! The event_watch is reading from `20260326` (yesterday) data! Look at:\n- `source_date_tag: \"20260326\"` — the data source is from 20260326\n- `freshness_status: \"pending_today_refresh\"` — it's waiting for today's refresh\n- `precheck_path`, `orders_path`, etc. all point to `20260326` files\n\nAnd the halt_reason says \"盘中门禁触发 halt: 3/4 指数下跌，盘中的门禁触发 halt\" — this is an intraday halt from yesterday's data.\n\nSo the P1-001 findings are not actually about today's strategy report — they're about yesterday's event_watch which is still showing the old halt state because today is a new day and the fresh data hasn't been incorporated yet.\n\n\nThe root cause is that `paper_execution_status` is being populated with stale data from 20260326 instead of today's date. I need to check how `make_summary` is constructing this object to understand why it's pulling in yesterday's information instead of waiting for today's refresh to complete.","thinkingSignature":"7bafaa963cb2b96ec7e3b3d7b44f79fd50189562e182856b4b4cf35df13392a3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8i2k0lcpkgcg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def make_summary\\|paper_execution_status\\|source_date_tag\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_investment_research_event_watch.py 2>/dev/null | head -10; grep -rn \"source_date_tag\\|paper_execution_status\" ~/.openclaw/skills/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".pyc\" | head -5","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64778,"output":353,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88163,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774584049200,"responseId":"061533f11bd6cc90eab4dfefc9736a2b"}}
