{"type":"message","id":"9cef36d7","parentId":"603156cd","timestamp":"2026-03-27T04:02:22.160Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but now there's another issue. The fallback block uses `effective_date_tag` but `trade_date_text` (from `report_obj.get(\"trade_date\")`) would be today's date if the strategy report was regenerated. So the fallback condition would be `trade_date_text == effective_date_tag` which is true, but `not latest_runtime` would be false (since `latest_runtime` is populated).\n\nActually wait - if `latest_runtime` is truthy (which it is since we fixed the date_tag issue), then `not latest_runtime` is False, so the fallback block won't execute. Good.\n\nBut I need to reconsider: the original fallback block was checking `trade_date_text == date_tag`. `date_tag` was `20260326` (from paper_date_tag). \n\nThe strategy report's `trade_date` would be `2026-03-27`, so `trade_date_text = \"20260327\"`, which wouldn't match `date_tag = \"20260326\"`, so the fallback wouldn't run. With my fix, `effective_date_tag` becomes `\"20260327\"` from the runtime_obj's date_tag, making `trade_date_text == effective_date_tag` true. But then `not latest_runtime` is false since runtime has data, so the fallback still doesn't execute—which is correct behavior. Let me verify the syntax is valid.","thinkingSignature":"29d81c684d106e5676f64ac87c18af64c1c6f8fddaea56a33d58ac3cc2919b61"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hf9alp9ut46f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -m py_compile scripts/run_investment_research_event_watch.py && echo \"语法OK\"","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69288,"output":344,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92664,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774584132573,"responseId":"06153444b5b2bdc672f0b9d58817f2ae