{"type":"message","id":"0bedfffa","parentId":"2b52d89b","timestamp":"2026-03-27T10:17:09.528Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tester reads the dated `today_stock_strategy_report_{date_tag}.json` at line 66, which has the old `normal/False` values. The close bundle updated `today_stock_strategy_report_latest.json` but not the dated version. The issue is that the dated file was not updated when the close bundle ran.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the close bundle log - it ran at 15:20 and wrote to `today_stock_strategy_report_latest.json`. But the dated file `today_stock_strategy_report_20260327.json` still has the morning values (`normal/False`).\n \nSo the root cause is that `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` only updates the `latest` symlink but leaves the dated file stale, and `generate_control_tower_daily.py` isn't writing a new dated file either. I need to verify whether the dated file even exists from the morning run or if it's missing entirely.","thinkingSignature":"a1704f5a1ef32ddecd68c16233d5674195d8bd81306979e63f4b1ba553bc5d01"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tv8nep8muts7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json, pathlib\ndt = '20260327'\nbase = pathlib.Path('quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports')\nd1 = base / f'today_stock_strategy_report_{dt}.json'\nd2 = base / 'today_stock_strategy_report_latest.json'\nprint('dated mtime:', d1.stat().st_mtime if d1.exists() else 'missing')\nprint('latest mtime:', d2.stat().st_mtime if d2.exists() else 'missing')\n\"","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":62561,"output":345,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85938,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774606620822,"responseId":"06158c1c3a7fb39baa1647d4bdb5795d"}}
