{"type":"message","id":"f217b650","parentId":"b8b54558","timestamp":"2026-03-27T10:17:46.442Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The close bundle doesn't seem to run `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py`. The `today_stock_strategy_report_latest.json` was updated at 15:20. Let me check what the `generate_control_tower_daily.py` does when it runs. Maybe it writes the `today_stock_strategy_report_latest.json`.\n\nActually, wait - looking at the log, it just shows the output file list, not which scripts ran. Let me check the bundle more carefully. But I notice the log shows `today_stock_strategy_report_latest.json` was updated at 15:20 - this was likely done by the `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` when it was run as part of the morning cycle (around 11:56) and then again in the afternoon (around 15:20).\n \nSo the dated file at 11:35 AM has `risk_mode=normal, halt=False`, while the latest version at 15:20 shows `risk_mode=halt, halt=True`. The tester is still reading the older dated file because it's comparing the wrong timestamp. The issue is that `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` writes both the dated and latest versions with the same content, but the close bundle at 15:20 only updated the latest copy, leaving the dated file stale.\n\nI need to trace when `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` was actually called today to understand why the dated file wasn't refreshed.","thinkingSignature":"bb8be7f1f447d50e66a5df8dd767dcb26f4496ba1665ffe224fea4ffdf93138a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a4yykqdgz2hq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"today_stock_strategy_report_20260327.json\\|today_stock_strategy_report_latest\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/logs/*.log 2>/dev/null | grep \"15:\" | head -10","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65421,"output":381,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTok