{"type":"message","id":"aee81f04","parentId":"f3d6ffca","timestamp":"2026-03-27T10:17:54.969Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me just check the mtime of the dated file and the generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py to understand the sequence of events. The key issue is that the tester at 18:16 reads the dated file (with stale data) while the latest file (updated at 15:20) has correct data.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The close bundle ran at 15:20 and produced `today_stock_strategy_report_latest.json` with `halt=True`. The dated file `today_stock_strategy_report_20260327.json` was produced by the morning run at 11:35 with `halt=False`.\n\nThe question is: why did the close bundle not regenerate the dated file? \n\n\nLooking at what the close bundle actually runs—it orchestrates various scripts but doesn't call `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` directly. When the control tower generates at 15:20, it's likely only writing to the latest file, not regenerating the dated version. The real fix would be to ensure the dated file gets written with the same halt state as the latest, or better yet, have the tester read from the latest file instead. Both fixes would resolve the inconsistency.","thinkingSignature":"9b329747d3c3df5efd3d860be31821f03f25df5d64c5ea04cecb78d0fda12a6a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vj3b1u8lpvwc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"20260327\\|latest_report_path\\|dated_report\" scripts/run_tester_scheduled_guard.py 2>/dev/null | head -15","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65820,"output":316,"cacheRead":23032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89168,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774606666565,"responseId":"06158c4a179a798e4035c1cad16201b0"}}
